The vocational training takes place on the one hand in the company and on the other hand in the vocational school.
In the company, you are 40 hours a week and therefore 8 hours a day.
At the vocational school 8 classes of 45 minutes each take place in theoretical lessons.
In order to pass the training, exams must be taken at the end.
The examinations and the monitoring of the training run over the Chamber of Industry and Commerce.
At the vocational school you have subjects like for example social studies, ethics, German and English language as well as word and data processing.
In the company one has different tasks, for example dealing with incoming and outgoing mails, sort and file away documents, organize different evevents and taking the minutes.
My favorit subject is German because I like to learn something new about spelling and grammar.
At the company I enjoy preparing and participating in events best because it is very diverse and, unlike the paperwork, it provides a bit variation.
Lately I bought a macbook for studying web design.
Current my job is not related with professional use of design, but someday I would like to have such job.
