I remember as if it were yesterday when I first listened to Dire Straits.
I was at a party when I heard a breathtaking solo guitar.
Since then, my dream was always to attend one of its concerts.
Dire Straits had given many concerts in my city but for one reason or another, it had never been possible for me to attend one of their shows.
I had been waiting for more than 30 years and now my dream was going to come true.
However, I started having doubts about whether or not after having expected for so long, the concert would really live up to my expectations.
The evening of the event, I put on my old black leather jacket and went to the football stadium where the concert was to take place in.
When the concert began everything and everybody around me disappeared.
There was nothing but the group and me.
However, the best was yet to come; the solo guitar that I had heard that very first day was longer and more intense than in any of their albums.
If I had to choose a single word to describe this experience, that would be undescribable.
In a nutshell, that day I learnt that no matter how well music sounds in the comfort of your own home, there is nothing like attending a concert.
Musicians playing live always go the extra mile to satisfy their audience.
